e the source material in historical and biographical context. Passages are accompanied by detailed notes and are organized around events, such as the Great Fire of Rome, or by topic, such as Nero's relationships with his wives. Complex events like the war with Parthia-split up among several chapters in Tacitus's Annals-are brought together in continuous narratives, making this the most comprehensible and user-friendly sourcebook on Nero available.Some images inside the book are unavailable due to digital copyright restrictions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Mai 2019) 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh1 aBarrett, Anthony A., eeditor.1 aFantham, Elaine, eeditor.1 aYardley, John C., eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2016z978311063859240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400881109zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400881109.jpg  a978-3-11-063859-2  PUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA21UPPPUP  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA9PRIN